 {"id":"beads_rust-nh5h","title":"Implement Theme with semantic colors and styles","description":"# Task: Implement Theme

## What to Do
Create the Theme struct that EXTENDS the existing color patterns in `src/format/text.rs`.

## File to Create
`src/format/theme.rs` (NOT src/output/theme.rs)

## CRITICAL: Reuse Existing Color Patterns
The codebase already defines colors in `src/format/text.rs`:
- Status colors: green (open) → yellow (in_progress) → red (blocked) → gray (closed)
- Priority colors: red+bold (P0) → red → yellow → gray
- Type colors: task (cyan), bug (red), feature (green), epic (magenta)
- Icons: ○ ◐ ● ❄ ✓ ✗ 📌

**DO NOT DUPLICATE** - import and extend these patterns.

## Design Philosophy
The theme provides SEMANTIC colors - colors that have meaning in context:
- Success: green (aligns with open/completed)
- Error: red (aligns with blocked/bug)
- Warning: yellow (aligns with in_progress)
- Info: cyan (aligns with task type)
- Accent: magenta (aligns with epic type)

## Implementation

```rust
//! Theme definitions for beads_rust CLI styling.
//!
//! EXTENDS existing color patterns from text.rs - do not duplicate!

use rich_rust::Style;
use crate::model::{Status, Priority, IssueType};

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct Theme {
    pub success: Style,     // Green - matches open status
    pub error: Style,       // Red - matches blocked/bug
    pub warning: Style,     // Yellow - matches in_progress
    pub info: Style,        // Cyan - matches task type
    pub dimmed: Style,      // Gray - matches closed/deferred
    pub accent: Style,      // Magenta - matches epic
    pub highlight: Style,   // Bold white
    pub issue_id: Style,
    pub issue_title: Style,
}

impl Theme {
    pub fn status_style(&self, status: Status) -> Style;
    pub fn priority_style(&self, priority: Priority) -> Style;
    pub fn type_style(&self, issue_type: IssueType) -> Style;
    pub fn status_icon(&self, status: Status) -> &'static str;
}
```

## Consistency Check
The Theme MUST produce visually consistent output with existing text.rs functions.

